    <p class="lead">The Web Toolkit provides several ways
    for laying out your web application according to your user's needs.
    This contains wrapping containers, a Bootstrap-based grid system,
    a powerful Drawer component, and responsive utility classes.</p>

    {{> table-of-contents data=toc}}

    <h2 id="containers" class="docs-h3">Containers</h2>

    <p>As in Bootstrap, you have two containers available. The default
    one should always be the ordinary <code>container</code>, which restricts
    your content to a certain width depending on your viewport.
    This behavior is perfect for all sort of informational websites,
    because it keeps things readable.</p>

