    {{/code-snippet}}

    <h2 id="grid" class="docs-h3">Grid</h2>

    <p>The AXA Web Toolkit uses the 12-column Bootstrap grid. Whenever
    you use the grid to split some content into multiple columns, make
    sure you place it inside a `container` or `container-fluid`.</p>

    <p>You can find the full documentation of the grid in the official
    <a href="{{gridDocs}}">Bootstrap grid docs</a>.</p>

    <h2 id="drawer-component" class="docs-h3">Drawer component</h2>

    <p>Especially on small screens, it's often necessary to
    toggle some content that slides into the viewport.
    The most common example
    is the menu that is toggled by a burger (ùç´) button. But there
    are also some cases in which that behavior needs to be available
    on larger screens, too. These docs are a great example for both those
    cases.</p>

    <p>In order to achieve such a behavior, there's the flexible
    Drawer component. It's fully documented in it's own
    <a href="{{relative '/layout/drawer/'}}">Drawer component docs</a>.</p>

    <h2 id="responsive-utilities" class="docs-h3">Responsive utilities</h2>

    <p>While you can use the Bootstrap v3 ones,
    we strongly recommend to already use the
    <a href="{{responsiveUtilsDocs}}">Bootstrap v4 responsive utilities</a>.
    Both are part of the AXA Web Toolkit.</p>

    <p>Reponsive utilities are CSS classes that allow you to hide content
    from a page depending on the user's current viewport. They can also be
    used to toggle content when printed.</p>

    <p>Try to use these on a limited basis and avoid creating entirely
    different versions of the same site. Instead, use them to
    complement each device's presentation.</p>

